  <textarea
    id="output"
    class="w-full p-4 border rounded shadow-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-green-500 h-60"
    placeholder="Output will appear here"
    readonly></textarea>
  <div class="flex justify-center space-x-4 mt-4">
    <button
      id="copy"
      class="bg-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded shadow w-48"
      >Copy to Clipboard</button
    >
  </div>

  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-6">
    <!-- Intro Section -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-lg">
        Welcome to our
        <strong>Base64 Encode/Decode Tool</strong> - the fastest and easiest way
        to convert text and binary data to and from Base64 format. Whether you're
        protecting sensitive information or simply ensuring data integrity, our free
        online Base64 tool provides a user-friendly interface with lightning-fast
        results.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What is Base64? -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What Is Base64 Encoding?</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Base64 encoding</strong> is a method of representing binary data
        (such as images, files, or other media) in a textual format. It takes the
        original data, splits it into smaller chunks, and converts it into a series
        of ASCII characters. This process ensures that the data can be safely transmitted
        and stored in systems that only handle textual information. By encoding data
        in Base64, you reduce the risk of corruption that may occur if raw binary
        data is sent through email or other text-based protocols.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Why Use Base64? -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Why Use Base64?</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-8 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Data Integrity</strong> - When sharing files via text-based channels,
          Base64 helps preserve the original content without alterations or errors.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Compatibility</strong> - Email clients, web APIs, and certain databases
          often require ASCII-friendly data. Base64 encoding ensures maximum compatibility
          across platforms.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Security</strong> - While not a form of encryption, Base64 obscures
          data to a certain extent, preventing casual observers from easily reading
          it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Efficiency</strong> - Base64 provides a compact, standardized format
          ideal for embedding data in HTML, CSS, or JSON.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- How to Use the Tool -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
        How to Use Our Base64 Encode/Decode Tool
      </h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal ml-8 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Paste or Type Your Data</strong> - Enter your text or binary file
          content into the input field.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Choose Encode or Decode</strong> - Select whether you want to convert
          your data <em>to Base64</em> or <em>from Base64</em>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Click the Button</strong> - Press the <em>"Encode"</em> or <em
            >"Decode"</em
          > button and watch the result appear instantly.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Copy or Download</strong> - Copy the converted string or download
          the file output whichever suits your needs.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-4">
        Our tool is designed for effortless usage. We've optimized it for speed,
